<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-02T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.51/253</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-02T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your July 28, 11 a.m. What information referred to in Department’s
                                July 13, noon [July 19, 4 p.m.] have you received from Cuban
                                Government as to loan?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>